Decrypt file to make sure you have it in a txt form

gpg --decrypt /nfs/local/admin/conf/admin/gpg/stuff.txt.gpg > siggy.txt
gpg -c siggy.txt 

Will ask for a pass phrase...and create a siggy.txt.gpg
**************************

IT DOESN'T DELETE THE ORIGINAL TXT FILE

**************************

rm -f siggy.txt

gpg --decrypt /nfs/local/admin/conf/admin/gpg/siggy.txt.gpg 

Pass phrase:

